        <num>CCRP 857</num>
        <heading>857.  Effect of granting new trial</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 857.  Effect of granting new trial
The effect of granting a new trial is to set aside the verdict or judgment and to permit retrial of the case with as little prejudice to either party as if it had never been tried.</p>
        </content>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
